headline: Summit Insights ups Western Digital to Buy on favorable demand-supply dynamics
summary: As previously reported, Summit Insights upgraded Western Digital (WDC) to Buy from Hold. While Western Digital is trailing Buy-rated Seagate (STX) in HAMR technology, the firm thinks the company’s Shingled Media Recording technology gives it legs to remain competitive in the market in the short-to-medium term. headline: Western Digital is now a Buy at JPMorgan following its latest earnings release
summary: Investing.com -- JPMorgan moved Western Digital (NASDAQ:WDC) to an Overweight rating from Not Rated and set a December 2025 price target of $57 per share in a note Thursday.
